@Hardroch 
....and this thing in the stock that tells time?

Asking for a friend.

@Bruce 

???

Does that make your time atypically slow or atypically fast?

@Oikofuge 

I don't know much about her music (or fashion), but Nicki MINAJ shows up often enough in these puzzles to make it worth learning her name.

Amusingly, MINAJ is pronounce very much like the French ménage.

@The X-Phile 

Plus she has been in the news a few times over the past few years (or so).

For me, it is a name that is fairly easy to remember, even though I know nothing about her music.

@The X-Phile 

Thanks. While I'm always keen to learn new words, I'm appallingly bad at remembering  people's names---the bit of my brain that stores vocabulary seems to be compressing the bit that stores names.
No offence to Ms Minaj, but I think if she comes up again I'll still have to rely on my crossword wiles.

@Oikofuge 

Thank you. 

I know almost nothing about Latin, and it never occurred to me that gender was playing a role here.

@JB 
This Scot was flummoxed by TAM. The only tams I knew of are worn to keep dreadlocks under control, and they're rarely tartan.
If we're talking about traditional Scottish caps, they're "tammies" or "tam o' shanters". I've never heard them called "tams".

@Michelle 

You make a good point that sometimes the clue gives you an additional hint, in case the answer is something you’ve never heard of and have to infer it. 

Recognizing this will help a solver move up a level!

@Steve L and Michelle,

It's so true. I briefly had just ADOWS (I waited a bit on entering HARRIS because Kamala and one other person(!) have six-letter names) and so I thought it might be something ending with meaDOWS, so I tentatively entered that but when I could see it wouldn't work, I looked back at the clue and the creepy part gave it away. I remember the show but not any of the character names.

Not that meadows can't be creepy...  The Maleficent Meadows: Vengeance of the Grasslands—coming soon to a theater near you.

@Steve L 
Thanks for the bread explanation. I don’t eat any bread but I do like the smell of the fresh baked stuff.
I was being a bit tongue in cheek with my %. It was more to say that we don’t get that much cosmopolitan food choices in the sticks. It’s white or brown. What more do you need?!

@Charlie 

I remember seeing movies and cartoons where someone slapped a person in the face and said I challenge you to a duel, or something like that.

It was almost a cliche in the 1960s or 70s.
